label: ABCB1, P2Y12, CES1, GPIIIA, B4GALT2, and PON1
ACS and/or PCI (includes PCI for ACS and non-ACS elective PCI)
non-ACS, non-PCI cardiovascular indications such as peripheral arterial disease and stable coronary artery disease following a recent myocardial infarction outside the setting of PCI

Neurovascular disease includes acute ischemic stroke or transient ischemic attack, secondary prevention of stroke, or prevention of thromboembolic events following neurointerventional procedures, such as carotid artery stenting and stent-assisted coiling of intracranial aneurysms
